    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "The Chicano Movement",
          "textSize": "heading-two"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "The Chicano Movement was a social and political movement in the 1960s and 1970s where Mexican Americans across the United States fought for their civil rights and defined their cultural identity. As Montejano was born in 1950, she turned 18 and graduated from high school in 1968, during the peak of the movement. San Antonio is a cradle of Mexican American culture, and this made it a hotbed of political activism during the movement as well. Montejano dove into it without hesitation."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "One particular item on the agenda of activists was education. As they had long been discriminated against in schools, Chicanos fought for educational equality in a number of ways. This included “walkouts,” where students would boycott school by physically walking out of class and refusing to attend school, often protesting as they did so. The walkouts happened across the country, but some of the most prominent in Texas were those at Edgewood ISD schools in San Antonio, as well as the Crystal City High School walkouts in Crystal City Texas. Montejano was involved in both to various degrees, despite the fact that she was not a student in either district."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "grid",
      "layout": [
        4,
        2
      ],
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "column",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "image",
              "url": "https://www.tshaonline.org/images/handbook/entries/EE/edgewood-high-school.jpg",
              "caption": "Edgewood High School in San Antonio Texas, circa 1965. Photo courtesy of the Texas State Historical Association website.",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
