                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "column",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "image",
              "url": "https://lrl.texas.gov/scanned/members/photos/large/B/Bernal_J_59.jpg",
              "caption": "Joe Bernal circa late 1960s/early 1970s. Photo Courtesy of the Legislative Reference Library of Texas website.",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "\nMontejano also interned with Joe Bernal, a Chicano politician who served in both the Texas State Senate and Texas State House of Representatives. Bernal was focused on educational policy improvement, including the Texas Bilingual Education Act."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Montejano worked under Bernal at the Guadalupe Community Center, a nonprofit on San Antonio’s Westside. While there, she completed social work in the city of San Antonio aiming to help improve educational prospects for Mexican Americans. This included the Young Careers Club, aiming to help Chicano middle schoolers pursue advanced careers, rather than just technical ones as the schools had previously channeled them towards. She also completed various research to help with legislative efforts as part of the Mexican American Legislative Caucus, which Bernal was a part of."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "\n"
        }
      ]
    },
